data.name: AccessStatement
data.value: Any restrictions on access to or use of the collection such as privacy certification or distribution restrictions is indicated here.

data.name: AnalysisUnit
data.value: The entity being analyzed in the study or in the variable

data.name: Authors
data.value: Name of the Principal Investigator or lead author and Name(s) of additional author(s)

data.name: ConfidentialityStatement
data.value: Please include a note about whether all or only some uploaded materials should be restricted. If some, indicate which files and the reason. E.g., “restrict access to “data.dta” because of geospatial information included or because of personally identified information (PII).

data.name: DataSource
data.value: Original sources or documents from which data were obtained, e.g., Authors, U.S. Census (Dublin Core: Source)

data.name: DataSourceInformation
data.value: Data source contact information

data.name: DataType
data.value: Nature of the data; kind of data documented in the logical product(s) of a study unit.

data.name: DepositAgreement
data.value: Please sign

data.name: Description
data.value: Brief description or abstract of the study, project, published article, or data collection; Include a brief statement of the study hypotheses

data.name: EmbargoStatement
data.value: Please include a note about whether all or only some uploaded materials should be restricted due to a request for embargo, along with the month/year at which materials may be released.

data.name: FieldDate
data.value: Date(s) of data collection

data.name: FundingInformation
data.value: Name of the funding agency and any additional information: date grant was received, grant number, etc.

data.name: InclusionExclusionCriteria
data.value: Criteria for participant selection, or study sample construction, including eligibility, inclusion and exclusion criteria

data.name: Intervention
data.value: Describe key details of the intervention and include all treatment groups. Include the number of intervention groups (enter 1 for single-arm study). Must be sufficiently detailed to distinguish between arms of a study and/or among similar interventions, and to describe any combinations of interventions; link to chart in cases where the intervention design is complicated.

data.name: InterventionAdministration
data.value: Describe how interventions were administered

data.name: IsRestrictedConfidential
data.value: Restricted due to confidential information

data.name: IsRestrictedEmbargo
data.value: Restricted due to embargo if materials should be embargoed for specified time period

data.name: IsRestrictedOther
data.value: Restricted due to another reason

data.name: Keywords
data.value: Words or phrases that best describe the study, project, published article, or data collection. Keywords help users find studies in the database. Use controlled vocabulary terms where appropriate. Be as specific and precise as possible. Avoid acronyms and abbreviations.

data.name: Location
data.value: Location about which data were collected

data.name: LocationDetails
data.value: Please enter more specific information such as country/countries. Only include information that may be made public in a catalog record; geospatial units at the level of small geographic areas such as villages may not be shared here.

data.name: ModeOfDataCollection
data.value: Describe how data were collected

data.name: Number
data.value: An organization-defined number for the item

data.name: Organization
data.value: Name of Institution with which the Author(s) is/are affiliated

data.name: OutcomeMeasures
data.value: Key measurement(s) or observation(s) used to measure the effect of experimental variables in a study, or for observational studies, measurement(s) or observation(s) that are a focus of the study (or the "dependent variable"); Include secondary and other measurements used to evaluate interventions, or, for observational studies, that are a focus of the study, excluding post-hoc measures.

data.name: OwnerContact
data.value: Contact information for Author

data.name: RandomizationProcedure
data.value: Describe how participants are allocated to intervention arms

data.name: RelatedDatabase
data.value: Data also deposited elsewhere (e.g., journal repository, institutional repository); Please provide a citation, DOI, or link

data.name: RelatedProjects
data.value: Registration of this study in a pre-analysis database (e.g., ClinicalTrials.gov, socialscienceregistry.org, http://egap.org/design-registration, etc.); Please provide a citation, DOI, or link

data.name: RelatedPublications
data.value: Scientific publication using the data deposited here (journal articles, books, book chapters, government and agency reports, working papers, dissertations, conference papers, meeting presentations, unpublished manuscripts, magazine and newspaper articles, and audiovisual materials); Please provide a citation, DOI, or link

data.name: ResearchDesign
data.value: The overall strategy for addressing the research problem(s)

data.name: ResponseUnit
data.value: The entity that provided the information carried by the variable

data.name: SampleSize
data.value: Number of subjects in the study or number of observations (actual); Sample size; Number of cases in the final public dataset

data.name: StudyTimePeriod
data.value: Date(s) covered in the study, project, published article, or data collection

data.name: Title
data.value: Name of this study, project, published article, or data collection

data.name: TotalObservations
data.value: Number of subjects in the study or number of observations (actual); Sample size; Number of cases in the final public dataset

data.name: UnitOfObservation
data.value: Who or what is being studied

data.name: UnitOfRandomization
data.value: Which units were randomized

data.name: VariableCategories
data.value: Label each value for categorical variables

data.name: VariableDescription
data.value: Question wording or more information
